<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showMessage?topicID=10604.topic">pub35.ezboard.com/fmonkly...0604.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upokiri.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pokiri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/1/02 2:25:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11689.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Amygdalan War Staff vs Tstaff</span><hr size=1> Prices on Prexus: AWS 50k, tstaff 35k. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umelestav.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Melestav</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/1/02 2:29:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11689.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.wkxx.com/robyn/fovcrest.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Amygdalan War Staff vs Tstaff</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the quick replies, that 5 page thread made my head hurt with a lot of speculating and little hard info. Oddly enough the prices on my server are almost opposite the 50k amy 35k tstaff.  I think i'll flip a coin and let decide, save me reading so much lol <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upokiri.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pokiri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 148<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/1/02 2:37:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11689.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Amygdalan War Staff vs Tstaff</span><hr size=1> I'd go with the cheaper one - they're both nice <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucrion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 313<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/2/02 6:11:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11689.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I chose Amy</span><hr size=1> I was faced with the same dilema earlier this week.  I nearly bought a T-Staff for 55k, but didn't because I really dont' want to deal with the 10wt and 55k seemed a bit high.  Having used a PB for 20 levels, I got fed up with the constant AC loss due to weight issues (I'm a bit of an AC junkie).<br>
<br>
The next day I saw an Amy War Staff for 40k.  Better ratio, better stats, and low weight.  I figured for the price, it was a good buy.<br>
<br>
So far I've used it a couple times and I'm liking the damage output.  <br>
<br>
I know the proc on the T-staff rules, but with a Druid bot, I feel that the proc is not as valuable to me at my level (52) as it would be at later levels when mobs hit for much more damage and riposte alot more.<br>
<br>
It was a pretty easy choice for me, and I'm happy I went with the T-Staff.<br>
<br>
Good luck!<br>
<br>
Hissteria <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usehnsuch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sehnsuch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/3/02 8:54:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11689.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I chose Amy</span><hr size=1> Do you mean to say you went with the Amygdalan War Staff? You're either very confused, or very misleading. <p><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=285468"> Roemy </a></br>50 Monk</br>Prexus</br>Endless Faith</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usaolin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saolin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/15/02 1:23:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11689.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> mmm</span><hr size=1> one Tstaff pro per minute = 3dps bonus, less or more depend on how many pro per minute<br>
<br>
if average 1 pro per minute and your have 60dps, that 3dps add like 5% more than 29/30 weapon<br>
<br>
what is difference between 37/36(0.9730) and 29/30(1.0345) weapon ? amy staff is 5.9% better ratio than staff, plus amy staff have more damage bonus which make it more better like 6%; now depend on Tstaff's pro, if it average pro twice per minutes then Tstaff better<br>
<br>
now, amy staff have good hp and weight bonus, tstaff's pro have good stun bonus which hard to compare <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukorph.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Korph</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 401<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/15/02 4:59:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11689.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: mmm</span><hr size=1> Shift is your friend.<br>
<br>
It has been parsed (over like 3 months of use, all logged) that Tranquil Staff with proc averages 106% of the dps of Tranquil Staff without proc.  Since stun time is not saved to logs (sans duels) it is hard to determine the average stun, but the range is from 0-12 seconds, making 6 seconds a good guess.  <br>
<br>
106% (120dd) * 29/30 (not a bad ratio!) + approx 2 stuns a minute for approx. 6 seconds each, reducing damage dealt to you by 1/5 (stunned for 12sec each minute) = Good weapon.<br>
<br>
Here's where I got the numbers from.  This information is not necessarily correct.<br>
<br>
120dd portion of proc upping damage by 6% = read from the long thread.<br>
29/30 = weapon ratio<br>
2 nukes a minute = You said 1 nuke a minute would up dps by 3%, so 6% increase = 2 procs/minute<br>
2 stuns a minute = see above<br>
average stun of 6 seconds = Speculated from average of 0 and 12.<br>
<br>
Flame away, FR is my best resist (see magelo).<br>
<br>
Edit:  Typos <p>-Korph
<br>
<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=308735"><img src="http://gjband.com/Sig.jpg"><br>Level 51 Disciple</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukorph.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Korph</A> at: 10/15/02 5:03:05 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usaolin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saolin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 147<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/16/02 1:16:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11689.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: mmm</span><hr size=1> from your parse, Tstaff's pro add 6%(2 pro per minutes):<br>
<br>
Tstaff = 29/30 + 6% DD + stun <br>
amy staff = 37/36(29/30 + 5.9% + %higher damage bonus) + HP<br>
<br>
this result make both weapon deal about <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> same damage output</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->; Tstaff is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> heavy(10wt)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and stun pro(2 pro every minutes) is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> big agro</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> but stun can save you some hit from mob(stun work well on low level mob, and useless on high level) ; amy staff is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> light weight(5wt)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and have <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> HP bonus</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> less agro</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
this result make me want amy staff more than Tstaff; Amy staff is more reliable damage and good for all situation, Tstaff need luck on pro(average 2 pro per minutes seen high for unbuff) and only good for solo/duo  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukorph.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Korph</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 419<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/16/02 1:33:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11689.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: mmm</span><hr size=1> Right you are.  <br>
<br>
Assuming equal DPS (They're pretty damn close)<br>
<br>
If agro and stunnage is what you want and can take the weight, Tranquiil Staff is your weapon.<br>
<br>
If you want less agro, +hp and stats, and light weight, Amyglydan War Staff is your weapon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ariane>Ariane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/16/02 1:35:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11689.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ummmmm</span><hr size=1> actually, most of the time i have my amy staff bagged, unless I'm pulling something big...where I need the extra hp. <br>
<br>
Contrary to what a lot of posters say, the main reason I use Tstaff is because the damage is more predictable than amy staff...sound counter intuitive?<br>
<br>
Well, its mainly because tstaff is a faster weapon.  Faster weapons will deal out damage on a &quot;smoother&quot; curve than hard hitting slower weapons.  <br>
<br>
Even without the proc, the damage is so close between the two weapons that I hardily notice any difference.  Add in the proc, and the tstaff comes ahead for me in most situations. <br>
<br>
Also, the proc is much more dependable than people think.  No, you can't predict precisely when it will go off.  However, you can count on it to regularly go off, and contribute a lot to damage.<br>
<br>
Last, I two box frequently.  In this scenario, tstaff comes out way ahead for me.  It saves me lots of mana on heals...mana, which instead of going to heals, is going to dots and nukes.  So net effect is I kill much faster and get more xp in long run.  <br>
<br>
Anyways, I'm sure there are plenty who likes amy staff more.  If you have either, you're set as they are both great weapons.<br>
<br>
Ariane <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umouse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mouse</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://people.netscape.com/rowley/pete.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/16/02 2:15:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11689.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> damage curves</span><hr size=1> Yup totally agree.  With my IFS or epic/SoS I can get the same streaks of misses, but with a high damage 2hb the same streak hurst DPS a lot more.  Sometimes it feels like Im not hitting the mob AT ALL.  So in all, faster weapons provide more predictable damage over the short term, even if the the slower ones give higher damage over the long term - that counts for nothing if you don't live to see it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showPrevMessage?topicID=11689.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showNextMessage?topicID=11689.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11689.topic&index=12><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.emailToFriend?topicID=11689.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.t